==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fraxinus
<hw>Frax"i*nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L., the
ash tree.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of deciduous forest
trees, found in the north temperate zone, and including the true ash
trees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <spn>Fraxinus excelsior</spn> is the European ash;
<spn>Fraxinus Americana</spn>, the white ash; <spn>Fraxinus
sambucifolia</spn>, the black ash or water ash.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fray</ent>⟦br⟧
